meanings.definition: Not final; not coming at the end.
meanings.sent1: The nonfinal decision left room for further changes.
meanings.sent2: Her nonfinal draft of the essay still needed revisions.
meanings.sent3: The nonfinal score in the game kept everyone on edge.
meanings.sent4: The nonfinal chapter of the book left readers eager for the conclusion.
meanings.sent5: The nonfinal design of the building allowed for adjustments to be made easily.

meanings.sent1: The nonfinal experiment results required more testing.

meanings.sent3: The nonfinal decision on the movie's ending puzzled the audience.
meanings.sent4: Her nonfinal opinion on the matter kept changing.
meanings.sent5: The nonfinal report raised more questions than answers.
